# Class names: readable and semantic

- **Do not** put raw CSS attribute values directly in class names.
- Use **readable, semantic** class names that describe purpose or component, not pixel/rem values.

## Avoid

- Arbitrary Tailwind values in `className`: `text-[10px]`, `gap-x-[3px]`, `rounded-[2px]`, `min-h-[90px]`, `w-64` (prefer a named size if it's a design token).
- Class names that are just the value: anything that reads like "10px" or "3px" in the class string.

## Prefer

- **Named utility or component classes** defined in CSS: e.g. `.activity-graph-month-label`, `.activity-graph-grid`, `.card-content-area`.
- In the CSS file, set the actual values: `font-size: 10px;`, `gap: 3px;`, `border-radius: 2px;`.
- Tailwind's **semantic utilities** when they match intent: `text-xs`, `text-muted-foreground`, `rounded-sm`, `gap-2`.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD – raw values in class name
<div className="text-[10px] gap-x-[3px] rounded-[2px] min-h-[90px]" />

// ✅ GOOD – readable class names, values in CSS
<div className="activity-graph-month-label activity-graph-grid activity-graph-cell" />
```

```css
/* In CSS */
.activity-graph-month-label { font-size: 10px; line-height: 1.25; }
.activity-graph-grid { display: grid; gap: 0 3px; }
.activity-graph-cell { border-radius: 2px; }
```
